# bhcom-ba (Angular 21)

Logistics SPA with **user** (`/`) and **admin** (`/admin`) portals. Prefer existing abstractions over new UI frameworks.

## App structure (`src/app/`)

Only three top-level folders — no `core/`, `features/`, or `layout/`:

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `shared/` | Auth, i18n, theme, `constants/`, `shell/`, `form/`, `table/`, `confirm/`, `ui/` — used by guest and portal |
| `guest/` | Unauthenticated routes, guards, login/register/portal-picker pages |
| `portal/` | Authenticated shell, configs, guards, features |

Paths below are relative to `src/app/` unless prefixed with `src/`.

## Import boundaries

- `shared/**` — import anywhere (guest + portal).
- `guest/**` → imports `shared/**` only (URLs via `shared/constants/app-urls.ts`). Do not import portal configs or features.
- `portal/user/**` ↔ `portal/admin/**` — **no** cross-import of features or routes.
- Feature HTTP: colocate `*.service.ts` in the feature; promote to `portal/{user|admin}/data/` when shared within one portal.

## Commands

- `npm start` — dev server (4200)
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm test` — run existing Vitest suite only when asked; see **Testing** below

## Testing (agents)

- **Never add unit tests** — no new `*.spec.ts` files, Vitest cases, test helpers, or test-only dependencies.
- Do not scaffold, suggest, or include unit tests as part of feature work, refactors, or bug fixes unless the user explicitly requests tests.
- Do not extend or rewrite existing unit tests unless the user explicitly asks.
- Prefer manual verification (`npm start`, `npm run build`) over adding coverage.

